From: Stephen Lang <skl@users.noreply.github.com>
Date: Fri, 10 Jul 2026 01:57:22 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 2/3] feat(jsonnet): add jsonnet implementation of the tsqtsq
 API

Hand-written port of src/promql.ts and src/expression.ts for jsonnet
consumers (monitoring mixins in particular). The API mirrors TypeScript
one-to-one: single params objects with the same field names, plain string
returns, so consumer code reads near-identically in both languages.

Behavioural equivalence is enforced by replaying the recorder-generated
conformance corpus (spec/fixtures/) via scripts/test-jsonnet.sh; error
cases are asserted per-case since jsonnet has no try/catch.

Two ordering behaviours are pinned as deterministic spec decisions
(jsonnet objects have no insertion order): Expression applies values in
lexicographic label order, and offset() emits units in canonical
descending order. Both are documented in jsonnet/README.md.

Install as a jb dependency:
  jb install https://github.com/grafana/tsqtsq/jsonnet@main
